{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"source": "pdfs/Population-synthesis-using-incomplete-microsample.pdf", "page_numbers": "[5]", "headings": "['4. Model Evaluation and Discussion']"}, "page_content": "4. Model Evaluation and Discussion\nTo validate the effectiveness of our proposed approach for training WGAN-GP with incomplete data, we initially utilized the h-nomis dataset to optimize the hyperparameters of the WGAN-GP model. Subsequently, we applied the same optimized parameters to train other models with h-miss-q-r datasets. The models underwent training on a GPU cluster comprising four NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3080 units, each with 10GB of memory, for a total of 1000 epochs. Figure 1 details the optimized model parameters.\nUltimately, the best-performing models were evaluated against the h-population dataset. To assess the models, we generated synthetic populations named Gnomis and Gmiss -q -r using the model trained on the h-nomis and h-miss-q-r datasets, respectively. All these synthetically generated populations consist of 5,156,896 data points.", "type": "Document"}}